description: Get late orders used to help system to avoid order cancellation and penalize scores

parameters.name: partner_id
parameters.description: Shopee's unique identifier for a partner

parameters.name: timestamp
parameters.description: The timestamp of making the request. Required for all requests. Expires in 5 minutes

parameters.name: access_token
parameters.description: Required for all endpoints. Valid for multiple use and expires in 4 hours

parameters.name: shop_id
parameters.description: shopee's unique identifier for a shop

parameters.name: sign
parameters.description: Authentication signature calculated based on parameters

request_parameters.name: page_no
request_parameters.description: Specifies the page number if data to return at current call. Starting from 1. If data is more than one page, page_no can be used together with page_size.

request_parameters.name: page_size
request_parameters.description: Each result set is returned as a page of entries. Use this parameter to control the maximum number of entries to retrieve per page. Default is 10, maximum is 100.

response_fields.name: error
response_fields.description: Indicate error type if an error. Empty if no error happened

response_fields.name: message
response_fields.description: Indicate error detail if Error. Empty if no error happened

response_fields.name: request_id
response_fields.description: The identifier for an API request for error tracing

response_fields.name: late_by_days
response_fields.description: Late by Days of the order

notes: The documentation includes Common Parameters, Request Parameters, Response Parameters, Request Example, Response Example, Error Codes, and API Permissions sections. The API appears to be part of Shopee's Account Health system for managing late orders.
